              interaction strength can shift the theory of multispecies
              communities from identifying the vast range of possibilities to
              isolating the most likely possibilities. To derive generality in
              our understanding of interaction strengths, however. they must be
              placed within a unified framework, a framework that can be applied
              to empirical situations. In this paper we first identify four
              different theoretical concepts of in eraction strength prevalent
