  volume   =  83,
  number   =  6,
  pages    = "1509--1520",
  abstract = "The theory of r- and K-selection was one of the first predictive
              models for life-history evolution. It helped to galvanize the
              empirical field of comparative life-history and dominated thinking
              on the subject from the late 1960 through the 1970s. Large
              quantities of field data were collected that claimed to test
